    <description>Extensions to HtmlHelper for things like checkbox lists, adds support for most to HTML5 input types and provides a fluent strongly-type way of specifying attributes.</description>
    <summary>Extensions to HtmlHelper for things like checkbox lists, adds support for most to HTML5 input types and provides a fluent strongly-type way of specifying attributes.</summary>
    <releaseNotes>Enhancements:
* Added support for input type="submit" by using the methods SubmitInputButton and SubmitInputButtonFor.
* Add support for the button element by using the methods Button and ButtonFor for button type="button" and SubmitButton and SubmitButtonFor for button type="submit".
* Also added BeginButton, BeginButtonFor, BeginSubmitButton and BeginSubmitButtonFor to allow you to specify html content as the value of the button.
* Added CheckBoxListItemLabel and CheckBoxListItemLabelFor for creating labels for checkboxes created with CheckBoxListItem and CheckBoxListItemFor.</releaseNotes>
